turn \"All dynamic-access call sites are covered.\"\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0-b05/execution-metrics.json:16:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0-b05/execution-metrics.json:21:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0-b05/execution-metrics.json:26:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0-b05/execution-metrics.json:61:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 14.59\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/stats.json:7:          \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/stats.json:12:          \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/stats.json:17:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:63:- Schedule-driven: full metadata sweep every three days to prevent incomplete or breaking metadata from shipping in releases, new-library-version compatibility (every six hours), Docker image vulnerability scans, scheduled release every two weeks, scheduled coverage publication.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:73:`publish-scheduled-coverage.yml` derives, from committed `stats/` and `metadata/**/index.json`:\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:75:- `COVERAGE.md` — the per-library coverage table linked from the README. Each\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:77:  `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/index.json` file and the dynamic-access coverage\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:83:sync with the generated coverage table through the bulk-update PRs created by\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:85:badge, graph, and history artifacts are published to the `stats/coverage` branch.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:90:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:93:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:104:| `library-update-request` | Issue / PR | Request or PR to improve support for an already-covered library, including coverage-improvement work. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:223:- **FR-T-7** Dynamic-access coverage between consecutive tested versions of a library must not regress (enforced by reviewer skills `review-fixes-javac-fail`, `review-fixes-native-image-run-fail`, `review-fixes-java-run-fail`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:263:- **NFR-7 Auditability.** Every Forge run produces a schema-validated metrics record; every coverage publish writes to a force-pushed branch with retained history.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:278:- Mirrored stats under `stats/`, a generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:8:    \"strategy_name\": \"javac_iterative_with_coverage_sources_pi_gpt-5.5\",\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:17:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:22:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:27:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:57:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:62:            \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:67:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:103:      \"code_coverage_percent\": 14.18,\n./stats/org.glassfish.hk2/hk2-api/2.5.0/execution-metrics.json:104:      \"previous_library_coverage_percent\": 14.59\n./stats/com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-cbor/2.14.3/stats.json:6:      \"coverageRatio\" : 1.0,\n./stats/com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-cbor/2.14.3/execution-metrics.json:15:        \"coverageRatio\": 1.0,\n./stats/com.fasterxml.jackson.dataformat/jackson-dataformat-cbor/2.14.3/execution-metrics.json:49:      \"co